"{\"uid\": \"rte.ie-sport-hockey-2024-0120-1427699-irelands-olympic-games-dream-ended-by-great-britain\", \"text\": \"Ireland 1-2 Great Britain  Ireland's hopes of making it to the Paris Games were ended in Valencia on Saturday afternoon as a clinical Great Britain dug out a 2-1 victory in their women's hockey Olympic qualifier third/fourth-place play-off.  On Thursday, Sean Dancer's Green Army werebeaten by Spain in a penalty shootoutin the semi-finals. Had they won, they would have sealed a ticket to the Games.  Instead they were consigned to a winner-takes-all play-off battle with Great Britain, who looked more dangerous throughout a tense clash.  Just over two minutes into the second quarter, Sarah Jones broke the deadlock, forcing home a shot after Ireland had failed to fully deal with a penalty corner.  Ireland's hopes of reaching the Olympics are ebbing away as Great Britain double their lead in the final quarter in Valencia\\ud83d\\udcfa Watch live -https://t.co/wsbcdnxLgT\\ud83d\\udcf1 Updates -https://t.co/kV2G4rYXJLpic.twitter.com/uYyo77Rsky  The Irish were dealt another major blow in quarter three when star player Deirdre Duke was forced off with an injury.  Forty seconds into the final quarter, their fate was sealed as Katie Robertson slotted a good finish beyond Ayeisha McFerran to net her ninth international goal.  Ireland huffed and puffed to the end and did get one back with the final play of the game, Hannah McLoughlin squeezing home from the edge of the circle.  However it was too little too late, with Great Britain celebrating raucously at the final whistle.  On Sunday, Ireland's men's team will chase a place at the Games when they take on Korea in a third/fourth-place play-off [2.30pm pushback].  Ireland:Ayeisha McFerren, R\\u00f3is\\u00edn Upton, Niamh Carey, Sarah Hawkshaw, Katie Mullan (Capt), Hannah McLoughlin, Naomi Carroll, Ellen Curran, Charlotte Beggs, Katie McKee, Beth Harper  Subs used:Sarah McAuley, Michelle Carey, Sarah Torrans, Elena Neill, Chloe Watkins, Deirdre Duke, Liz Murphy (GK)  Great Britain:Sabbie Heesh, Lily Owsley, Anna Toman, Hannah French, Sarah Jones, Sarah Robertson, Isabelle Petter, Giselle Ansley, Hollie Pearne-Webb (Capt), Fiona Crackles, Sophie Hamilton  Subs used:Amy Costello, Elena Rayer, Tessa Howard, Katie Robertson, Laura Roper, Lily Walker  \\u00a9 RT\\u00c9 2026. RT\\u00c9.ie is the website of Raidi\\u00f3 Teilif\\u00eds \\u00c9ireann, Ireland's National Public Service Media. RT\\u00c9 is not responsible for the content of external internet sites.  Images Courtesy of Getty Images.\"}"